main event: On February 22, 1961, a brilliant, round tapered cone-shaped object was observed over Silver Bay and Gilbert, Minnesota.
interesting points: Conflicting reports described the object as a fire or bright meteor., One observer noted the object flashed a bright light before exploding and disintegrating., The explosion was preceded by a sound described as a 'rush of air', The object broke into 3 or 4 pieces before disappearing behind trees., Observers noted that the object was brilliant enough to be seen during daylight.
witness description: Mr. Garfield Gulbranson, a policeman; Mrs. Joanne Gulbranson, a housewife; and a deputy sheriff.
